      <Statement>Use tiling to show in a concrete case that the area of a rectangle with whole-number side lengths &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;b&lt;/i&gt; + &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt; is the sum of &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt; &amp;times; &lt;i&gt;b&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;a&lt;/i&gt; &amp;times; &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt;. Use area models to represent the distributive property in mathematical reasoning.</Statement>
